An Act
ENROLLED HOUSE
BILL NO. 3465 By: Boles and Hill of the House
and
Green of the Senate
An Act relating to revenue and taxation; amending
Section 7, Chapter 346, O.S.L. 2022 (68 O.S. Supp.
2025, Section 55012), which relates to the
termination date for the Oklahoma Emission Reduction
Technology Incentive Act; increasing termination date
by three years; and providing an effective date.
SUBJECT: Revenue and taxation
BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
SECTION 1. AMENDATORY Section 7, Chapter 346, O.S.L.
2022 (68 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 55012), is amended to read as
follows:
Section 55012. The Oklahoma Emission Reduction Technology
Rebate Program shall cease on July 1, 2027 2029.
SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.

Passed the House of Representatives the 24th day of February,
2026.
Presiding Officer of the House
of Representatives
Passed the Senate the 4th day of May, 2026.
Presiding Officer of the Senate
